Photoperiod table for a given year and location/latitude

Source: R/photoperiod.R
photoperiod_year.Rd

Returns daily daylight length (hours) for the specified year.

Usage

photoperiod_year(
  year,
  lat = NULL,
  location = NULL,
  aggregate = c("none", "month")
)

Arguments

year

Integer year (e.g., 2020).

lat

Latitude in decimal degrees. Ignored if location is supplied.

location

Optional location key; case-insensitive, ignores spaces/punct. Aliases like "saint johns" also work for "st_johns".

aggregate

Return daily values ("none") or monthly means ("month").

Value

data.frame with columns: date, daylength_hours, lat, location.

Examples

# Daily photoperiod for 2020 at 47.56°N (St. John's, NL)
photoperiod_year(2020, lat = 47.56)
